sudo rm -rf /usr/local/go
Download the Latest Go Version: Visit the Go Downloads page to confirm the latest version and replace go1.xx.x below with the latest version:

bash
Copy code
wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.23.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz
Extract the New Go Version: Extract the downloaded archive into /usr/local:

bash
Copy code
sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.23.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz
Update PATH (if necessary): Ensure your PATH environment variable includes /usr/local/go/bin. Add this line to your ~/.profile or ~/.zshrc:

bash
Copy code
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin
Reload the profile:

bash
Copy code
source ~/.profile
Verify the Installed Version: Confirm the new version of Go is installed:

bash
Copy code
go version
